CNCP v1 23437
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13159: CSS nesting and `:deep()` in scoped styles not working",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:04.145869+00:00",
  "text": "CSS nesting and `:deep()` in scoped styles not working\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.13\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nLet's display it.\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe background color of `hoge1` will turn red.\nThe background color of `hoge2` will turn green.\n\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe background color of `hoge1` will not turn red.\nThe background color of `hoge2` will turn green.\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nVue 3.5.13\nTypeScript 5.8.2\n\nbrowser microsoft edge 134.0\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nOriginal style content before conversion\n```css\n.base1 {\n  :deep(.hoge) {\n    background-color: red;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis is how it should be:\n```css\n.base1 {\n&[data-v-7ba5bd90] .hoge {\n    background-color: red;\n}\n}\n```\n\nIn reality, this is what happened:\n```css\n.base1 {\n[data-v-7ba5bd90] .hoge {\n    background-color: red;\n}\n}\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: compiler",
    "has workaround",
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
